1
00:00:00,520 --> 00:00:01,970
[Episode 11]

2
00:00:11,260 --> 00:00:14,160
Why are you just standing there? Come in.

3
00:00:46,150 --> 00:00:48,570
Get in, you little brat.

4
00:00:49,410 --> 00:00:50,810
And you call yourself a man?

5
00:00:50,900 --> 00:00:53,010
[How dare you!]

6
00:00:53,410 --> 00:00:55,700
You don't want to? Say that again.

7
00:00:56,360 --> 00:00:59,040
Must I seem like a loser because of you?

8
00:00:59,130 --> 00:01:00,410
Must I?

9
00:01:01,070 --> 00:01:03,180
You inept piece of trash!

10
00:01:03,270 --> 00:01:05,770
Do you know what should become
of useless brats like you?

11
00:01:15,850 --> 00:01:18,310
Jun, open up!

12
00:01:18,670 --> 00:01:21,440
[Jun, open this door!]

13
00:01:21,530 --> 00:01:23,370
-Don't.
-Jun, open the door!

14
00:01:23,460 --> 00:01:25,000
-Let go.
[-Jun!]

15
00:01:25,090 --> 00:01:26,500
-Father, stop this.
-Move!

16
00:01:26,590 --> 00:01:28,039
-Let go of me.
-Please stop.

17
00:01:28,130 --> 00:01:29,670
-You won't let go?
[-Jun!]

18
00:01:29,970 --> 00:01:31,950
-Open this door!
-Father!

19
00:01:32,039 --> 00:01:33,009
Let go!

20
00:01:33,100 --> 00:01:34,680
Jun!

21
00:01:35,560 --> 00:01:36,750
You little...

22
00:01:44,759 --> 00:01:45,950
Jun-wan.

23
00:01:50,390 --> 00:01:51,490
Jun-wan?

24
00:01:54,000 --> 00:01:55,140
Leave us.

25
00:01:57,430 --> 00:02:00,070
Jun-wan, you see...

26
00:02:03,720 --> 00:02:04,870
Go.

27
00:02:05,130 --> 00:02:06,270
Jun-wan...

28
00:02:18,770 --> 00:02:21,720
Jun-wan, it's not like you saw.

29
00:02:25,770 --> 00:02:26,820
You.

30
00:02:27,880 --> 00:02:30,340
Have you been beating him behind my back?

31
00:02:31,350 --> 00:02:32,890
Jun-wan, listen to me.

32
00:02:34,829 --> 00:02:36,280
I warned you

33
00:02:37,780 --> 00:02:39,850
that Jun's off limits.

34
00:02:40,329 --> 00:02:43,060
But that little brat

35
00:02:43,280 --> 00:02:44,770
acted out--

36
00:02:50,710 --> 00:02:52,120
You've gotten weaker.

37
00:02:53,440 --> 00:02:54,810
It hurts me to see that.

38
00:02:58,240 --> 00:02:59,470
Doesn't this get old for you?

39
00:03:04,530 --> 00:03:06,600
Haven't you done this enough?

40
00:03:08,360 --> 00:03:11,090
Just stop, darn it!

41
00:03:20,370 --> 00:03:21,470
What's going on?

42
00:03:22,700 --> 00:03:25,560
Tell me what's going on! Where's Jun-wan?

43
00:03:32,470 --> 00:03:33,570
Jun-wan?

44
00:03:34,630 --> 00:03:36,079
Jun-wan, open up.

45
00:03:36,560 --> 00:03:38,060
Jun-wan, open this door!

46
00:03:38,150 --> 00:03:40,740
Open this door, Jun-wan. Jun-wan!

47
00:03:40,829 --> 00:03:43,210
Jun-wan, no!

48
00:03:43,290 --> 00:03:44,880
Jun-wan, open this door!

49
00:03:47,780 --> 00:03:49,010
This is that day all over again.

50
00:03:50,200 --> 00:03:53,770
Ever since that day,
Jun-wan shut down completely.

51
00:03:54,070 --> 00:03:55,390
He no longer laughed.

52
00:03:56,100 --> 00:03:57,150
No...

53
00:03:57,240 --> 00:03:59,840
Jun-wan, open this door! Jun-wan!

54
00:03:59,930 --> 00:04:01,070
Jun-wan!

55
00:04:10,270 --> 00:04:11,670
Mommy.

56
00:04:13,040 --> 00:04:15,370
Mom, I'm sick.

57
00:04:15,590 --> 00:04:17,529
Step aside, darn it!

58
00:04:18,100 --> 00:04:20,250
Jun-wan, please open this door.

59
00:04:20,339 --> 00:04:21,490
Jun-wan...

60
00:04:28,170 --> 00:04:30,510
Hello? Hello?

61
00:04:30,640 --> 00:04:31,870
Please...

62
00:04:32,659 --> 00:04:35,520
Please save my son.

63
00:04:37,240 --> 00:04:39,659
Please save my son.

64
00:04:46,920 --> 00:04:48,770
Jun-wan, oh no.

65
00:04:48,850 --> 00:04:51,800
[Youth Villa]

66
00:05:01,970 --> 00:05:03,110
Hey, So-bin.

67
00:05:03,240 --> 00:05:06,370
Soo-hyun, is Jun back?

68
00:05:06,540 --> 00:05:07,600
Not yet.

69
00:05:08,300 --> 00:05:11,820
He's unreachable at the moment
and I'm worried.

70
00:05:11,910 --> 00:05:13,980
I'll tell him to call you
when he gets back.

71
00:05:16,490 --> 00:05:18,550
-Soo-hyun.
[-Yes?]

72
00:05:22,650 --> 00:05:24,230
It probably won't be of help,

73
00:05:25,510 --> 00:05:26,960
but I can at least listen.

74
00:05:28,810 --> 00:05:29,990
At times,

75
00:05:32,190 --> 00:05:34,570
Jun seems miles away.

76
00:05:37,340 --> 00:05:39,320
I want to close the distance,

77
00:05:41,870 --> 00:05:44,690
but I'm worried
that maybe it's not something

78
00:05:47,420 --> 00:05:48,690
he wants.

79
00:05:51,550 --> 00:05:55,510
If you're patient,
he might close the distance himself.

80
00:05:57,409 --> 00:05:58,770
That's who he is.

81
00:06:00,490 --> 00:06:01,670
[I bet that didn't help.]

82
00:06:04,010 --> 00:06:05,110
It did.

83
00:06:06,600 --> 00:06:08,760
Thanks, Soo-hyun.

84
00:06:25,170 --> 00:06:28,340
What will happen to Father?

85
00:06:28,910 --> 00:06:32,650
He'll be punished
and the world will know about him.

86
00:06:36,740 --> 00:06:38,110
So this is what it comes to.

87
00:06:38,370 --> 00:06:40,790
Once the media gets wind of this,
your life will be disrupted.

88
00:06:43,470 --> 00:06:44,530
It's all right.

89
00:06:45,540 --> 00:06:46,730
I'm no stranger

90
00:06:48,090 --> 00:06:49,330
when it comes to fame.

91
00:06:53,370 --> 00:06:55,880
I made up my mind the day I found you

92
00:06:57,770 --> 00:06:59,010
passed out from his beating.

93
00:06:59,840 --> 00:07:03,890
That I'd protect you from him.

94
00:07:08,160 --> 00:07:10,970
I thought I only had
to cope with him alone.

95
00:07:17,570 --> 00:07:19,730
That I only had to keep you out of range.

96
00:07:22,770 --> 00:07:24,390
I believe it'd then be all right.

97
00:07:27,830 --> 00:07:28,970
Jun-wan.

98
00:07:32,270 --> 00:07:33,500
I'm sorry.

99
00:07:36,930 --> 00:07:39,090
It made things worse for you.

100
00:07:46,610 --> 00:07:48,900
You used to be a pretty boy
as bright as the sun.

101
00:07:52,909 --> 00:07:55,330
I'm still unbelievably pretty, you know.

102
00:07:57,000 --> 00:07:58,230
So don't worry.

103
00:07:59,640 --> 00:08:00,960
I'll shake this off

104
00:08:02,540 --> 00:08:04,650
and live a happy life.

105
00:08:06,630 --> 00:08:08,350
As if nothing had happened.

106
00:08:13,010 --> 00:08:15,130
-What about you?
-What?

107
00:08:15,210 --> 00:08:17,060
What about your life?

108
00:08:18,380 --> 00:08:20,410
You never did anything you wanted

109
00:08:21,950 --> 00:08:24,150
and went down the path
our parents wanted for you.

110
00:08:27,360 --> 00:08:28,460
I'm fine.

111
00:08:29,030 --> 00:08:31,710
You should live your life
doing what you want to.

112
00:08:31,890 --> 00:08:33,080
That doesn't exist.

113
00:08:34,880 --> 00:08:36,380
You should go on a date too.

114
00:08:38,710 --> 00:08:40,340
How do I do that?

115
00:08:44,780 --> 00:08:45,970
Take your own advice

116
00:08:47,110 --> 00:08:49,230
and build a healthy relationship
with So-bin.

117
00:08:49,800 --> 00:08:52,480
I'd rather you do things
that are less by-the-book.

118
00:08:52,970 --> 00:08:54,240
Got it?

119
00:08:55,830 --> 00:08:57,150
I'll be watching you.

120
00:09:06,170 --> 00:09:07,270
I'll get going then.

121
00:10:00,200 --> 00:10:01,470
Get going.

122
00:10:02,260 --> 00:10:04,420
I always walked away
without seeing you off.

123
00:10:05,920 --> 00:10:07,150
Head inside.

124
00:10:09,130 --> 00:10:10,710
I won't until you go.

125
00:10:36,140 --> 00:10:38,520
[The only way to protect you from him]

126
00:10:39,180 --> 00:10:40,900
[was to live the life that he wanted.]

127
00:10:41,950 --> 00:10:43,450
You go ahead and live your life.

128
00:10:44,460 --> 00:10:45,650
Freely.

129
00:10:52,640 --> 00:10:53,830
[Thanks.]

130
00:10:54,400 --> 00:10:56,210
[Thanks for the lift]

131
00:10:56,740 --> 00:10:58,540
[and the advice.]

132
00:10:58,670 --> 00:11:01,220
[But moreover, thanks for reminding me]

133
00:11:01,310 --> 00:11:03,070
[that you're a psychopath.]

134
00:11:12,310 --> 00:11:13,850
[What gives you the right to say that?]

135
00:11:14,510 --> 00:11:16,670
[You beat the crap out of me!]

136
00:11:17,550 --> 00:11:19,440
I see you've already
erased it from your memory,

137
00:11:21,290 --> 00:11:22,960
but I'm reminded of it every day.

138
00:11:23,310 --> 00:11:26,480
So don't you dare forget about it
without my permission.

139
00:11:34,220 --> 00:11:40,160
[Youth Villa]

140
00:11:40,250 --> 00:11:44,650
[Youth Villa]

141
00:12:25,260 --> 00:12:26,450
You're home.

142
00:12:33,140 --> 00:12:34,330
What's wrong?

143
00:12:42,340 --> 00:12:43,480
Jun.

144
00:12:46,520 --> 00:12:49,640
Are you all right?
So-bin's worried sick about you.

145
00:12:57,820 --> 00:12:59,100
What's going on?

146
00:14:26,620 --> 00:14:29,390
[My Jun]

147
00:14:34,400 --> 00:14:36,250
[Youth Villa]

148
00:16:08,740 --> 00:16:11,470
[Myungil University]

149
00:16:13,840 --> 00:16:16,660
The classroom feels empty without Jun.

150
00:16:19,040 --> 00:16:20,840
My eyes are bored.

151
00:16:21,940 --> 00:16:23,790
Don't tell me you still--

152
00:16:23,880 --> 00:16:27,130
Of course not.
It's just how you feel with celebrities.

153
00:16:28,060 --> 00:16:29,380
Why hasn't he been to school?

154
00:16:29,460 --> 00:16:32,370
Ask Kim So-bin.
Being his girlfriend, she'd know.

155
00:16:42,090 --> 00:16:43,680
[Aren't we being too obvious?]

156
00:16:44,030 --> 00:16:46,180
That's exactly how I want to be.

157
00:16:46,840 --> 00:16:48,820
So that everyone knows we're a couple.

158
00:17:03,780 --> 00:17:06,069
Soo-hyun, why are you standing here?

159
00:17:06,819 --> 00:17:08,140
I was waiting for you.

160
00:17:09,369 --> 00:17:10,520
-Me?
-Yes.

161
00:17:12,010 --> 00:17:14,740
I thought you'd like some company
since Jun's not here.

162
00:17:16,280 --> 00:17:18,700
So you'd eat lunch with me in his place?

163
00:17:20,020 --> 00:17:21,960
When did I start speaking casually to you?

164
00:17:23,319 --> 00:17:25,430
It didn't take you long with Jun.

165
00:17:26,579 --> 00:17:27,680
Is that so?

166
00:17:27,760 --> 00:17:29,660
I didn't know
you two would become friends.

167
00:17:32,160 --> 00:17:36,560
I bet me living with Jun
is uncomfortable for you.

168
00:17:37,750 --> 00:17:40,220
Hardly. I rather feel reassured.

169
00:17:42,990 --> 00:17:45,630
To know
he has someone like you by his side

170
00:17:46,820 --> 00:17:48,050
reassures me.

171
00:17:48,800 --> 00:17:50,200
But I can't pack a punch.

172
00:17:52,540 --> 00:17:54,600
Even when I'm not around,

173
00:17:55,660 --> 00:17:57,640
he has you beside him.

174
00:17:59,660 --> 00:18:02,300
He'll have moments to laugh thanks to you.

175
00:18:05,340 --> 00:18:07,320
Is that what is like
to have feelings for someone?

176
00:18:08,110 --> 00:18:12,070
You wish for that person's happiness
even when you're not beside them.

177
00:18:17,570 --> 00:18:19,640
Is there no one like that in your life?

178
00:18:20,920 --> 00:18:22,410
I doubt that's what you want to know.

179
00:18:23,730 --> 00:18:25,760
Why aren't you asking me how Jun's doing?

180
00:18:29,670 --> 00:18:32,750
Because talking about him
only makes me miss him more.

181
00:18:41,240 --> 00:18:42,610
Don't worry too much about Jun.

182
00:18:48,020 --> 00:18:49,820
Could that be Jun?

183
00:19:10,420 --> 00:19:11,510
I missed you.

184
00:19:43,550 --> 00:19:44,650
I missed you.

185
00:20:08,140 --> 00:20:11,620
Why are you still standing there
and ruining the mood?

186
00:20:12,410 --> 00:20:13,820
To hand you my class notes.

187
00:20:20,950 --> 00:20:22,130
Here you go.

188
00:20:22,400 --> 00:20:24,860
What's important are marked,
so keep that in mind.

189
00:20:26,400 --> 00:20:27,590
And here's mine.

190
00:20:28,510 --> 00:20:31,200
What's up with you two?
This isn't exactly what I need right now.

191
00:20:32,170 --> 00:20:33,440
Don't be ridiculous.

192
00:20:33,530 --> 00:20:35,820
After missing classes,
a student should make up for them.

193
00:20:37,180 --> 00:20:38,720
Whose notes will you take?

194
00:20:38,810 --> 00:20:41,320
You can only choose once
and you only get one chance to choose.

195
00:20:45,100 --> 00:20:47,350
Forget it. I'm done taking any classes.

196
00:20:48,230 --> 00:20:51,660
I have two people
who love me enough to take notes,

197
00:20:51,750 --> 00:20:53,200
so why bother?

198
00:20:53,290 --> 00:20:54,340
-No way.
-No way.

199
00:20:57,110 --> 00:20:59,710
Don't hang out with him.
He's rubbing off on you.

200
00:21:05,610 --> 00:21:06,880
[Professor Yeo Jun-wan]

201
00:21:07,890 --> 00:21:09,430
Always the mood-wrecker.

202
00:21:10,530 --> 00:21:11,680
Just a second.

203
00:21:12,380 --> 00:21:13,480
Yes, Professor.

204
00:21:27,560 --> 00:21:29,100
Are you feeling better now?

205
00:21:32,930 --> 00:21:37,640
I returned home that day after
everything was sorted with my father,

206
00:21:39,790 --> 00:21:42,080
but seeing you brought on the tears.

207
00:21:43,970 --> 00:21:45,820
What hurt me for a long time

208
00:21:46,350 --> 00:21:48,730
was no longer a big deal for me
which seemed futile.

209
00:21:50,840 --> 00:21:52,860
I guess the pain became my friend.

210
00:21:54,800 --> 00:21:58,630
I coped with it for too long.

211
00:22:00,780 --> 00:22:02,280
So leaving it behind

212
00:22:04,170 --> 00:22:06,370
felt like I was parting ways
with myself from the past.

213
00:22:09,190 --> 00:22:12,440
That's why you cried your eyes out.
From the pain of a breakup.

214
00:22:16,450 --> 00:22:17,680
We're even now.

215
00:22:18,470 --> 00:22:21,110
-What do you mean?
-I saw you cry too once.

216
00:22:22,470 --> 00:22:23,570
Me?

217
00:22:24,540 --> 00:22:25,860
I've never cried though.

218
00:22:29,510 --> 00:22:31,800
Then I guess you didn't.

219
00:22:33,560 --> 00:22:35,230
Maybe I saw you cry on the inside.

220
00:22:37,040 --> 00:22:39,190
That you should've about 100 times.

221
00:22:42,100 --> 00:22:43,370
[Waiting Room]

222
00:23:09,950 --> 00:23:11,270
Every now and again,

223
00:23:12,500 --> 00:23:14,350
I realize that clinging to you

224
00:23:16,150 --> 00:23:17,690
was the best thing I did.

225
00:23:18,930 --> 00:23:21,080
Yes, you have a knack for that.

226
00:23:22,670 --> 00:23:24,430
I actually can't do it well

227
00:23:26,010 --> 00:23:27,330
because I'm scared of rejection.

228
00:23:28,250 --> 00:23:29,490
Why did you do it then?

229
00:23:30,630 --> 00:23:31,950
I just wanted to.

230
00:23:33,840 --> 00:23:35,160
Are you speaking informally to me?

231
00:23:36,480 --> 00:23:38,680
I was deeply hurt back then, you know.

232
00:23:39,740 --> 00:23:41,230
But I'm glad I didn't give up.

233
00:23:42,470 --> 00:23:44,010
If I hadn't met you,

234
00:23:44,970 --> 00:23:46,690
I wouldn't have made it this far.

235
00:23:48,450 --> 00:23:51,660
I would've stayed as someone
who couldn't speak his heart.

236
00:23:53,950 --> 00:23:55,490
I guess I'm grateful in a way.

237
00:24:00,150 --> 00:24:02,310
What if I never met you though?

238
00:24:05,740 --> 00:24:06,970
I won't think about it.

239
00:24:09,880 --> 00:24:11,370
I really don't want to.

240
00:24:13,270 --> 00:24:14,940
While backed into a corner,

241
00:24:16,520 --> 00:24:18,990
I thought about ending it all.

242
00:24:20,350 --> 00:24:22,640
But I guess my ending
isn't mine to decide.

243
00:24:24,440 --> 00:24:25,720
Why else would I have met you?

244
00:24:28,710 --> 00:24:30,250
I guess I'm grateful in a way.

245
00:24:42,880 --> 00:24:44,550
-What's he doing here--
-Soo-hyun.

246
00:24:46,270 --> 00:24:47,590
I'll talk to him.

247
00:24:55,860 --> 00:24:56,960
I'm sorry.

248
00:24:57,050 --> 00:24:59,600
You should apologize to So-bin, not me.

249
00:24:59,690 --> 00:25:02,370
So-bin is who I'm here to apologize to.

250
00:25:04,000 --> 00:25:06,020
How else could I show my face at school?

251
00:25:07,210 --> 00:25:08,930
But then I spotted you

252
00:25:09,810 --> 00:25:11,210
and I owe you an apology too, so...

253
00:25:14,250 --> 00:25:17,020
I'll take time off school

254
00:25:19,180 --> 00:25:20,540
after this semester.

255
00:25:24,770 --> 00:25:26,260
You've changed.

256
00:25:26,350 --> 00:25:28,950
A trip to the police station
knocks sense into you.

257
00:25:30,090 --> 00:25:31,940
I looked back on my past choices.

258
00:25:33,350 --> 00:25:34,580
It's scary there.

259
00:25:36,120 --> 00:25:37,920
I don't want to even go near one again.

260
00:25:39,110 --> 00:25:41,400
My life as a student here is over.

261
00:25:42,590 --> 00:25:45,400
I'll be a ghost
and disappear once I graduate.

262
00:25:49,360 --> 00:25:50,680
As if you're dead?

263
00:25:51,030 --> 00:25:53,590
You make people around you so miserable.

264
00:25:54,330 --> 00:25:56,970
If you behave yourself,
we'll have no problems at all.

265
00:25:57,060 --> 00:25:59,040
Live like you're dead.

266
00:25:59,130 --> 00:26:01,020
Don't create a roadblock for your brother!

267
00:26:05,380 --> 00:26:07,270
You shouldn't ruin your life like that.

268
00:26:09,690 --> 00:26:11,630
-What?
-Make it right.

269
00:26:12,510 --> 00:26:14,400
Everyone can start over, you know.

270
00:26:18,800 --> 00:26:20,340
-Jun--
-Although,

271
00:26:21,220 --> 00:26:22,630
enough with the violence.

272
00:26:23,860 --> 00:26:25,400
That only leaves wounds.

