00:41:43,500 --> 00:41:45,960
I got dumped
when I didn't even confess, right?

532
00:41:47,410 --> 00:41:49,970
I'm not going to answer that.
It hurts me more.

533
00:41:50,190 --> 00:41:52,830
Hey, you're crueler than him!

534
00:41:54,850 --> 00:41:56,650
How about we help each other?

535
00:41:58,460 --> 00:42:01,140
When we have the urge to call our crush,

536
00:42:02,150 --> 00:42:03,650
we call each other instead.

537
00:42:05,280 --> 00:42:06,990
So we'll be each other's substitute?

538
00:42:07,080 --> 00:42:09,900
Yes. We have to help each other.

539
00:42:25,560 --> 00:42:28,030
[M Foods CEO's wife
reports him for domestic violence.]

540
00:42:54,340 --> 00:42:58,560
[CEO Yeo Myung-hoon]

541
00:43:13,740 --> 00:43:14,840
Secretary Kim.

542
00:43:15,850 --> 00:43:17,040
Get in here!

543
00:43:18,540 --> 00:43:19,770
Secretary Kim!

544
00:43:23,420 --> 00:43:24,610
Where is everyone?

545
00:43:26,460 --> 00:43:27,560
Secretary Cha!

546
00:43:33,850 --> 00:43:35,080
Honey, I'm home.

547
00:43:37,110 --> 00:43:38,650
You should come greet your husband.

548
00:43:40,190 --> 00:43:41,510
Hey!

549
00:44:18,290 --> 00:44:21,410
She is out of her mind.

550
00:44:23,610 --> 00:44:24,980
She is definitely out of her mind.

551
00:44:54,680 --> 00:44:55,950
There's nothing in here.

552
00:45:01,630 --> 00:45:04,450
Maybe I should just order in.

553
00:45:11,440 --> 00:45:12,590
What?

554
00:45:12,670 --> 00:45:15,970
Did that smarty pants forget the passcode?

555
00:45:32,560 --> 00:45:35,160
Hey, where's your mom?

556
00:45:35,730 --> 00:45:36,830
Come out!

557
00:45:37,310 --> 00:45:39,290
Bring her to me now.

558
00:45:39,470 --> 00:45:41,890
Why are you looking for Mom?
You have no right.

559
00:45:42,860 --> 00:45:45,230
What? I have no right?

560
00:45:45,890 --> 00:45:48,050
Do you know what I'm going through
because of you?

561
00:45:48,140 --> 00:45:50,120
Why is that my fault? It's your own fault.

562
00:45:50,210 --> 00:45:52,540
How dare you talk back to me?

563
00:45:52,630 --> 00:45:55,050
So many people have suffered
because of your abusive behaviors.

564
00:45:55,530 --> 00:45:57,990
Why must you live like this? Why?

565
00:45:58,210 --> 00:46:00,500
You arrogant brat. Hey.

566
00:46:01,070 --> 00:46:02,750
Who's supporting you financially?

567
00:46:03,450 --> 00:46:06,790
Do you earn money? Whose money is this?

568
00:46:07,720 --> 00:46:09,390
Whose money is all this?

569
00:46:09,480 --> 00:46:11,940
Do you earn money
so you can have a reason to beat us?

570
00:46:12,820 --> 00:46:15,070
-What?
-Just get the punishment you deserve,

571
00:46:15,730 --> 00:46:17,880
apologize to everyone,

572
00:46:18,540 --> 00:46:20,080
and start over.

573
00:46:20,520 --> 00:46:21,840
You little...

574
00:46:22,460 --> 00:46:24,920
Enough, seriously!

575
00:46:26,110 --> 00:46:28,790
That kid who used to shudder in fear
after getting beaten up by you

576
00:46:28,970 --> 00:46:30,200
is dead now.

577
00:46:33,990 --> 00:46:36,320
If you lay a finger on Jun-wan
or Mom again,

578
00:46:36,760 --> 00:46:38,340
it won't end with just calling the cops.

579
00:46:39,090 --> 00:46:40,100
Hey.

580
00:46:42,130 --> 00:46:44,020
Even you look down on me now?

581
00:46:44,280 --> 00:46:47,360
Dad. Dad!

582
00:46:47,670 --> 00:46:49,560
That's all in your head!

583
00:46:51,810 --> 00:46:54,580
Please let it go
and stop being delusional.

584
00:46:56,510 --> 00:46:57,440
"Delusional"?

585
00:46:57,530 --> 00:46:59,290
No one looks down on you.

586
00:47:00,080 --> 00:47:02,500
You are the one
who looks down on yourself.

587
00:47:02,590 --> 00:47:04,960
You're torturing yourself!

588
00:47:35,150 --> 00:47:36,200
[Jun-wan.]

589
00:47:37,300 --> 00:47:38,490
Hey, Jun.

590
00:47:39,370 --> 00:47:42,490
[I just called to hear your voice.]

591
00:47:43,330 --> 00:47:45,270
Good. I'm glad you called.

592
00:47:49,580 --> 00:47:51,250
Is everything okay?

593
00:47:52,530 --> 00:47:53,580
Yes.

594
00:47:54,680 --> 00:47:55,780
Everything's good.

595
00:47:58,420 --> 00:47:59,520
Sweet dreams.

596
00:48:00,360 --> 00:48:01,460
You too.

597
00:48:20,070 --> 00:48:21,650
[Father, Incoming Call]

598
00:48:28,030 --> 00:48:29,220
Hello.

599
00:48:48,980 --> 00:48:51,700
I worked hard without a single day
of proper rest.

600
00:48:52,630 --> 00:48:54,920
I started out as the low man
on the totem pole

601
00:48:56,060 --> 00:48:59,230
and managed to become the CEO
with my skills and hard work alone.

602
00:49:00,770 --> 00:49:01,960
I did that for our family.

603
00:49:02,090 --> 00:49:04,290
I know you made a sacrifice

604
00:49:05,260 --> 00:49:07,100
so we could have a comfortable childhood.

605
00:49:14,320 --> 00:49:15,380
Jun-wan.

606
00:49:16,830 --> 00:49:18,940
Why do we have to live like this?

607
00:49:19,780 --> 00:49:23,910
Talk to your mom
and persuade her to come home.

608
00:49:25,410 --> 00:49:27,170
She always listens to you, you know.

609
00:49:29,630 --> 00:49:33,770
I love your mother.

610
00:49:35,350 --> 00:49:37,070
You and Jun too.

611
00:49:38,390 --> 00:49:40,020
I really love all of you.

612
00:49:43,360 --> 00:49:44,460
Is that

613
00:49:46,570 --> 00:49:48,420
"love" to you?

614
00:49:50,180 --> 00:49:51,100
What?

615
00:49:56,380 --> 00:49:58,500
We're no longer your family.

616
00:50:00,120 --> 00:50:02,540
No wife and no children.
You have no one now.

617
00:50:03,860 --> 00:50:07,380
-What?
-I should have said this to you back then.

618
00:50:11,610 --> 00:50:12,620
Instead,

619
00:50:14,730 --> 00:50:17,280
I said it to someone I love and hurt him.

620
00:50:20,100 --> 00:50:22,780
I'll make everything go back
to the way it was, although it's late.

621
00:50:22,870 --> 00:50:24,280
Do you think you won't be affected?

622
00:50:26,040 --> 00:50:27,890
Everyone at the university will find out.

623
00:50:32,380 --> 00:50:33,960
I don't care.

624
00:50:58,730 --> 00:51:00,890
[Idiot Nam Soo-hyun]

625
00:51:05,820 --> 00:51:07,440
[Wanted Criminal]

626
00:51:16,160 --> 00:51:17,080
[Girl With a Story]

627
00:51:17,170 --> 00:51:18,530
Who is she talking to?

628
00:51:19,460 --> 00:51:21,000
I hope it's not Nam Soo-hyun.

629
00:51:38,820 --> 00:51:39,920
Young-ran.

630
00:51:41,100 --> 00:51:44,140
-Yes?
-You must miss Mi-ju too.

631
00:51:47,700 --> 00:51:51,090
I'm sure she's doing okay.
She's a strong girl, you know.

632
00:51:53,910 --> 00:51:57,430
How about a beer? Just the two of us.

633
00:52:04,470 --> 00:52:05,610
Cheers.

634
00:52:13,580 --> 00:52:15,160
I can't even enjoy this beer.

635
00:52:16,920 --> 00:52:20,000
Is something bothering you?

636
00:52:21,670 --> 00:52:23,560
Will the person I like

637
00:52:25,100 --> 00:52:27,830
ever like me back, like a miracle?

638
00:52:31,970 --> 00:52:33,020
Miracles happen.

639
00:52:36,240 --> 00:52:39,450
I forgot for a moment
that you're a living example.

640
00:52:41,820 --> 00:52:43,100
Having a crush on someone...

641
00:52:43,890 --> 00:52:45,430
Looking back,

642
00:52:46,800 --> 00:52:48,640
I think it was more like a habit.

643
00:52:51,280 --> 00:52:55,460
Falling for someone, getting hurt,

644
00:52:56,120 --> 00:52:59,160
and feeling hopeful
about things that didn't even matter.

645
00:53:04,440 --> 00:53:08,880
Without Jun, I would've never been able
to quit that habit.

646
00:53:11,830 --> 00:53:13,680
Habits die hard.

647
00:53:16,500 --> 00:53:17,860
But such a miracle

648
00:53:19,660 --> 00:53:21,120
will happen to you as well.

649
00:53:22,570 --> 00:53:23,800
I'm sure of it.

650
00:53:26,880 --> 00:53:30,710
What does Soo-hyun mean to you?

651
00:53:33,040 --> 00:53:34,230
Soo-hyun is...

652
00:53:38,230 --> 00:53:39,990
The past seven years of my life.

653
00:53:40,700 --> 00:53:43,200
The past seven years
were all about Soo-hyun.

654
00:53:46,060 --> 00:53:48,220
Mi-ju reminds me of myself.

655
00:53:48,970 --> 00:53:51,170
And I envy her courage.

656
00:53:51,700 --> 00:53:55,350
I always thought I wouldn't be able
to do what she did,

657
00:53:59,530 --> 00:54:01,460
but I think it's time I gave up.

658
00:54:03,220 --> 00:54:04,320
Young-ran.

659
00:54:04,410 --> 00:54:06,960
Hey, why are you getting teary-eyed?

660
00:54:07,050 --> 00:54:08,590
I didn't know you were so empathetic.

661
00:54:09,870 --> 00:54:12,680
I'm just sad.

662
00:54:14,270 --> 00:54:15,980
I can't do it anymore
because I'm exhausted.

663
00:54:17,170 --> 00:54:18,930
I used to be always full of energy,

664
00:54:20,470 --> 00:54:22,580
but I can't go on
because I'm mentally exhausted.

665
00:54:29,320 --> 00:54:32,000
Hey, it's okay. I'm older than you.

666
00:54:32,090 --> 00:54:33,280
So what?

667
00:54:34,680 --> 00:54:36,800
I can't even comfort you
because I'm younger?

668
00:55:02,840 --> 00:55:04,080
Si-jae.

669
00:55:08,170 --> 00:55:09,360
What?

670
00:55:09,440 --> 00:55:11,200
I was wondering why he was so quiet.

671
00:55:12,390 --> 00:55:13,670
Where did he go?

672
00:55:14,280 --> 00:55:15,650
[Vitamin Drink]

673
00:55:17,670 --> 00:55:19,830
Take it easy.
You need to look after your health.

674
00:55:20,400 --> 00:55:22,780
I will. Thank you, Professor.

675
00:55:22,860 --> 00:55:25,590
By the way, what should I wear?

676
00:55:26,600 --> 00:55:28,410
You can wear whatever you want.

677
00:55:28,890 --> 00:55:29,950
Really?

678
00:55:30,520 --> 00:55:33,200
What kind of song
do you want to hear that day?

679
00:55:34,220 --> 00:55:35,980
Just pick something you're good at.

680
00:55:36,060 --> 00:55:39,890
I'm good at everything,
so there are too many to choose from.

681
00:55:41,520 --> 00:55:44,470
Just pick the song
you feel most confident with.

682
00:55:45,000 --> 00:55:49,130
Oh, I should try to look after my voice.

683
00:55:49,220 --> 00:55:51,240
But it's your event.

684
00:55:51,330 --> 00:55:54,190
What if I steal the spotlight
because everyone loves my voice so much?

685
00:55:54,590 --> 00:55:56,350
I'm already nervous.

686
00:56:02,770 --> 00:56:05,060
-Gosh, you scared me.
-Keep talking.

687
00:56:05,150 --> 00:56:07,390
Why did you suddenly stop talking
as soon as I walked in?

688
00:56:07,740 --> 00:56:09,990
We weren't really talking about anything.

689
00:56:11,660 --> 00:56:13,330
I was just talking to myself.

690
00:56:14,700 --> 00:56:15,840
Take it easy.

691
00:56:16,500 --> 00:56:17,640
Take it easy.

692
00:56:23,670 --> 00:56:24,770
Have a good day.

693
00:56:31,990 --> 00:56:33,180
Park Si-jae.

694
00:56:36,780 --> 00:56:38,630
-What's going on between you two?
-What?

695
00:56:39,780 --> 00:56:41,400
What are you suspecting?

696
00:56:41,490 --> 00:56:42,810
What you're thinking.

697
00:56:43,470 --> 00:56:44,620
Don't be absurd.

698
00:56:44,700 --> 00:56:46,380
Go apologize to Ms. Seol.

699
00:56:46,460 --> 00:56:48,660
Then what were you two whispering about?

700
00:56:48,750 --> 00:56:51,080
Just something, which I can't tell you.

701
00:56:54,160 --> 00:56:56,580
-Are you that curious?
-No, I'm not curious.

702
00:56:56,670 --> 00:56:59,360
I'm worried people would gossip.
It'll ruin your reputation.

703
00:56:59,930 --> 00:57:01,560
-What did I even do?
-Be careful.

704
00:57:02,130 --> 00:57:04,550
If you slip, you'll fall off the cliff.

705
00:57:08,600 --> 00:57:10,800
If I "slip"? What is she talking about?

706
00:57:13,830 --> 00:57:15,680
My joints are still healthy!

707
00:57:16,080 --> 00:57:17,440
[Strawberry Milk]

708
00:57:19,900 --> 00:57:22,460
You got this for me?

709
00:57:22,810 --> 00:57:25,180
If you prefer banana milk,
I'll go exchange it.

710
00:57:26,240 --> 00:57:28,970
-Are you my Secret Santa?
-Oh, no.

711
00:57:29,670 --> 00:57:31,390
I won't lie again.

712
00:57:32,880 --> 00:57:34,820
-Anyway, enjoy.
-Wait, Chun-guk.

713
00:57:40,800 --> 00:57:42,470
["Poems for the Heart"]

714
00:57:41,110 --> 00:57:44,190
Read one poem a day.

715
00:57:44,320 --> 00:57:45,600
It'll purify your heart.

716
00:57:45,690 --> 00:57:48,680
Did someone ask you to do this?

717
00:57:49,950 --> 00:57:51,760
No, I just wanted to give it to you.

718
00:57:51,850 --> 00:57:53,560
I thought you'd find the poems helpful.

719
00:57:55,150 --> 00:57:57,040
["Poems for the Heart"]

720
00:57:55,190 --> 00:57:56,550
A poetry book...

721
00:57:56,950 --> 00:57:58,840
Only Jung-ho would be this thoughtful.

722
00:57:59,150 --> 00:58:00,870
Oh, he must be my Secret Santa.

723
00:58:01,530 --> 00:58:03,680
Anyway, tell him I said thanks.

724
00:58:03,770 --> 00:58:04,910
Bye.

725
00:58:06,280 --> 00:58:07,770
I'm his Secret Santa.

726
00:58:08,870 --> 00:58:10,500
Am I not thoughtful?

727
00:58:15,520 --> 00:58:16,790
I gave it to her.

728
00:58:18,600 --> 00:58:21,150
-Here.
-Hey, it's okay.

729
00:58:21,500 --> 00:58:22,600
What's with you?

730
00:58:22,690 --> 00:58:26,300
I did it for free.
You don't need to be sorry. I'm off.

731
00:58:27,180 --> 00:58:29,030
Why is he acting all nice?

732
00:58:29,990 --> 00:58:32,720
Where is my Secret Santa?

733
00:58:37,610 --> 00:58:39,280
Soo-hyun saved seats for us.

734
00:58:39,370 --> 00:58:41,610
-Let's sit there.
-No, let's sit somewhere else.

735
00:59:07,790 --> 00:59:14,830
[Fashion Brand Z, Promo Video]

736
00:59:08,050 --> 00:59:09,290
Let's begin.

737
00:59:10,560 --> 00:59:14,480
We made a promo video for fashion brand Z.

738
00:59:14,570 --> 00:59:15,710
What's the brand tagline?

739
00:59:15,800 --> 00:59:18,350
The tagline is, "Don't look any further.
You are the answer."

740
00:59:19,760 --> 00:59:21,560
There's a girl who no one ever notices.

741
00:59:21,650 --> 00:59:23,760
She's a college freshman

742
00:59:23,850 --> 00:59:26,840
with no unique style or her own
or a good sense of fashion.

743
00:59:27,280 --> 00:59:29,220
But she meets a popular guy at her school

744
00:59:29,310 --> 00:59:31,770
who has tens of thousands of followers
on social media.

745
00:59:31,860 --> 00:59:34,280
This is a story of how
their encounter changes her.

746
00:59:34,670 --> 00:59:36,610
It's not just about fashion.

747
00:59:36,700 --> 00:59:39,690
We focused on her journey
of finding her true self.

748
00:59:40,170 --> 00:59:41,410
Let's watch the video.

749
00:59:45,540 --> 00:59:47,300
Let's talk about what we thought

750
00:59:47,390 --> 00:59:48,840
of the other teams' presentations.

751
00:59:50,250 --> 00:59:51,440
They were good.

752
00:59:51,790 --> 00:59:54,340
They were all creative,
and I liked their stories.

753
00:59:54,910 --> 00:59:56,190
Why do you ask?

754
00:59:56,760 --> 00:59:59,670
We won't get the highest mark
at this rate.

755
00:59:59,750 --> 01:00:01,030
You wanted the highest mark?

756
01:00:01,340 --> 01:00:03,230
He always gets the highest mark.

757
01:00:04,070 --> 01:00:05,960
We'll try to make our story stand out,

758
01:00:06,050 --> 01:00:07,370
but it has its limits.

759
01:00:08,510 --> 01:00:09,920
Do you have any other ideas?

760
01:00:11,770 --> 01:00:15,070
Then why don't we focus on casting?

761
01:00:16,300 --> 01:00:17,490
Casting?

762
01:00:45,070 --> 01:00:46,130
Excuse me.

763
01:00:46,970 --> 01:00:48,990
Are you Kim Hye-yoon
in Journalism and Communication?

764
01:01:27,620 --> 01:01:29,430
[At a Distance, Spring is Green]

765
01:01:29,510 --> 01:01:31,230
Kim So-bin!

766
01:01:31,320 --> 01:01:33,030
-Hold on.
-Let's do it again.

767
01:01:33,870 --> 01:01:35,280
Let's try that again.

768
01:01:35,370 --> 01:01:37,390
-One more time.
-Just this one scene.

769
01:01:40,690 --> 01:01:42,010
My gosh.

770
01:01:42,360 --> 01:01:44,390
-What's the matter?
-What was that sound?

771
01:01:44,470 --> 01:01:45,930
-Sorry?
-Try that again.

772
01:01:46,010 --> 01:01:47,070
Okay!

773
01:01:47,160 --> 01:01:48,390
It's okay.

774
01:01:48,480 --> 01:01:50,330
It's fun to tease him.

775
01:01:50,410 --> 01:01:52,310
You can do it with me. Bye, guys.

776
01:01:52,920 --> 01:01:54,150
Do what?

777
01:01:54,240 --> 01:01:55,780
-Wait.
-Cut.

778
01:01:56,710 --> 01:01:57,760
But...

779
01:01:57,850 --> 01:01:59,430
-Cut, good.
-Okay.

780
01:01:59,520 --> 01:02:00,620
What?

781
01:02:02,910 --> 01:02:04,360
Action!

782
01:02:06,030 --> 01:02:07,220
Where's Mi-ju going?

783
01:02:07,310 --> 01:02:09,550
-It's the other way.
-Oh, right.

784
01:02:11,270 --> 01:02:12,500
Let's do that again.

785
01:02:13,250 --> 01:02:14,790
Put it to a vote?

786
01:02:14,880 --> 01:02:16,420
Cut. Let's try that again.


